The paper presents a system based on deep feedforward neural network for time series anomaly detection. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories, as these are the most relevant areas for developing and applying neural network models. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category, as it involves the use of neural networks. The paper may also be relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category, as anomaly detection is an important problem in security and fraud detection. Finally, the paper may be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category, as it discusses the monitoring of Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) in internet companies and other organizations.
